  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Prove the feasibility of a needle forceps in patients with enlarged mediastinal lymph nodes
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Patients with enlarged mediastinal lymph nodes must be staged. The EBUS TBNA technique is an
      established technique. Unfortunately the size of the needle is limited to 21 gauge. With tne
      new designed needle forceps it should be possible to obtain more material and establish the
      diagnosis more often
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
